        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-05-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-05-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="964" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d964">
                <head>Official Song Union of Munsingen</head>
                <note rend="inline" rendition="#center" type="source">[Translation.]</note>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Munsingen</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-05-06">
                        <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 6, 1865</date>.</dateline>
                <p>The members of the Official Song Union, amounting to one hundred and fifty in
                        number, met in Konalfingen on the 30th of April, 1865, and resolved as
                        follows:</p>
                <p>The undersigned declare their deep sympathy in the general sorrow, on account
                        of the atrocious assassination of President Abraham Lincoln, and cordialy
                        rejoice at the happy consequences of northern victories in the North
                        American Union.</p>
                <p>They also request the proper execution of this resolution by the superior
                        authorities.</p>
                <p>In the name of the Union:</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <list>
                            <item>Z P. STÜNG, <lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">Notary, President</hi>.</item>
                            <item>JACOB FISCHER, <lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">Secretary</hi>.</item>
                        </list>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
